il painting in the distinctive style of Mian Situ, using thick palette knife texture and sharply defined contours, portraying a busy urban street scene in New York City during the 1960s. In the foreground, men in suits and fedoras and women in colorful dresses and gloves walk along the sidewalk, their figures catching late afternoon sunlight. Some are in motion, others chatting or window shopping, painted with expressive brushstrokes and rich shadow work. Classic cars from the era line the curb, painted in compact tones of mint green, cream, and cherry red. The street shimmers with reflections from nearby glass storefronts and chrome surfaces. In the background, mid-century buildings rise in tones of rust, steel blue, and oxidized gold, adorned with retro signage and vintage advertisements. Trees line the avenue, their leaves blending olive green and soft lilac into the warm urban light. The scene is full of movement and character, rendered in encaustic textures with bold palette knife strokes, capturing the energy, culture, and style of 1960s New York in the narrative realism of Mian Situ.
